What makes love last?
Adam Taha
Artist and writer passionate about psychology of dating · Author has 5K answers and 94.4M answer views · Updated 6y ·

18 years. 15 years. 10 years.

These are the years I’ve been in relationsip wIth lovers I am with right now. The thing is - even I don’t know what makes love last in relationships.

That’s the thing you see.

Vulnerability.

You know from experiences in your life, where you met someone, loved them and they loved you, but down the road, they completely changed or you find they are not who they are and the giving back is wanting.

It hurts. It makes your emotionally go crazy.

You do the most craziest things but it’s pain nevertheless. It’s dissappointments. It’s all those hours, times, you have given, invested and all you get back is..

A sentence.

It’s cold.

Emotionally cold.

It doesn’t matter what they say now, it doesn’t really matter anymore because you had enough and you’re not even going to explain. You don’t care. You gave it all and now, well..now..

It now all spirals down and…you’re back to square one.

And you hate what you become.

You hate how you behave.

You hate how you become someone you never really wanted to be because you know the good in you.

You know this isn’t really you but you’re so tired of loving someone who doesn’t love back, or you’re tired of giving and it is not appreciated in the way you want.

You’re tired if the selfish, self centred and the victim type of people. Tired of the holding back and walking of eggshells.

Tired of always thinking you know someone so well and then you find it was a charade, a mask they wore and you find you don’t even know this person at all. It seems so hard and tiring to find truth these days.

I suppose you can say, that because these events in your life has happened, you have empathy for someone who can’t love, or someone who is emotionally cold, or someone who is low in self esteem or someone who keeps jumping to the next big glitter shiny object but you’re also tired of showing empathy.

You’re tired of trying to control that which you can’t and you don’t know what is real anymore when people talk, connect, share and say the words of love so easily and some say it after a couple of days knowing you.

But you want to believe in the eternal flower of love.

You got to believe that love can conquer all or what else is there?

That love can fix this and that somehow love will make it all go away if..you can control this part of the person, that part of society, this part of life and that part of their beliefs.

The more you try, the more you see it so fragile like autumn leaves falling and no one gives a damn walking on those feelings and dreams of yours.

So it spirals down down into whatever void you shelve this memory. Deep, deep you fall and you feel no one can now reach you to pull you out.

And all you want to do is…sleep and forget and drown the memory of ever meeting each person you fell in love with.

Isn’t that what so many fear when it comes to dating, relationships, applying for jobs, business and life in general?

The fear of abandonment. The fear of rejection.

That what defines someone is external, That if someone loves someone else, it means they didn’t love them.

So many women and men asked me…

“How can a man love more than one woman.”

My reply is, “how can you not if you love for yourself inside is huge? Or do you feel that someone’s love is a measurement of your self worth, or how much they have for you? Isn’t that the reason why possessiveness and jealousy exist? To control people, the outcome because you fear being abandoned and rejected?”

For most people they get scared that someone can love aother. That someone will not love them anymore.

They do the craziest things when they are in that dark place.

They fear this happening again.

They’ve experienced someone abandoning them or rejecting the but they never learn then lesson.

It repeats throughout their life and so they always walk in the shadows of jealousy and possessiveness.

But everyday, I love with courage that is also vulnerable.

So do you everyday.

Everyday, you get up and do it all again with work, going for your goals, job, study and knowing, it can all fall apart.

You ask yourself..

“How long will this job last?

  • How long can I go on to achieve the goal in this current situation I am in?
  • How long can my partner take my goal driven dreams when I got not much to show for it? I am fighting with all my worth and yet it seems everything I do comes back with nothing.
  • Will I be able to be strong enough if it all goes away?
  • Will I still be standing if they walk away now?
  • Will I be able to stand beside my dreams then?
  • Will I be able to be the person I want to be?
  • Can they take me for who I am and the place I am in my life right now?
  • How long will their love last for me?
  • Is love really enough?
  • How long will I be valued in that job?
  • If I lose my job and all that it gets us, will his person still be with me when we face shit storm coming at us with bills, debts and so on?
  • Is being good at what you do enough?

Everyday, you give to your children in the hope they grow up knowing more than you, avoiding the mistakes you made and not see you as their enemy.

Hoping you did your best even though at times no one showed you how and you really don’t know you’re doing but you’re trying your best.

You hope they see, learn with understanding and don’t fly away too far.

You ask yourself..

  • How long will they love me as their father/mother?
  • How long will they keep coming back to see me?
  • Will they forget or be so busy to see once in a while?
  • Will they still want my help or will I be of no use to them when they grow?

You know so many things are out of your control,.

Even your own children as they grow.

Your job is not even certain.

You know your time in life might switch off.

You know your friends may change, or date someone, get serious, have no time for you like they used to and fly away.

They fade away like you didn’t even exist.

You know in all that you’ve seen, that whoever you care about, whatever you create and build might crumble before your eyes anytime time soon or not.

But don’t you get tired of always trying to control rather than to live in the moment, the now and present?

It’s like every start of something has to be planned, orchestrated before it happens, and all the judging, labeling is all about control.

Control sex

Control relationship.

Control how long it..lasts.

Have you noticed how mostly everything for us is about control?

Have you noticed that everything you try to control…slips through your fingers?

You might be in that same place again, in which you don’t want that person to go away, you wish they feel the same loving, affection, desire you have for them, with you.

You wish they touch you the way you do with them, say the words you want to always hear, kiss the way you want to always be kissed, make love to you the way you so want to without being judged.

To give that attention you give to them. Those letters, those creative videos, those works that took you hours to do but…they don’t.

Instead your talent, your time, your creativity, all that amazing giving you put into creating a moment in which you can hear them lavish you with so many words….

But all you get by is one sentence and you’re heart sinks.

You just cannot understand why they don’t give as much as you do. You cannot understand how they knew, KNEW, who you are, where you’re going in life and what you want.

I even some women say…

“Oooh I didn’t know sex is important to you!”

Se fucking read everything I write. She knows my lifestyle. She knows how I behave. She knew like it was crystal clear.

The same women who complain about not getting love and they get it and they tr to focus on their own insecurit8ies and say it how they didn’t know blah blah because they are avoiding the real issue.

So you get people in this position, loving someone to wonder…

Why….when they were in that place of pain, hurt they so complained about when they met you…and,…they know how it feels to love someone and they didn’t get loved back….they go off doing it to you?

Shouldn’t they know what it feels like to not be appreciated?

What you feared the most happens before right your eyes.

If all the people, it’s that person who said they never got loved. Of all the people you never thought would act this way, you find they are the ones who do.

You never saw it coming.

How can this be happening?

You realise, they haven’t got it in them.

They are all talk.

Talk like they do on social media in pretending they care about this, that. Talk but really they know not about love. They probably give only to pimp some image and not really give because they feel affection for someone.

You’ve cried many a times due to this.

You felt your heart ache and break into a thousand pieces because of this. The land of Oz is no more. The Eternal flower of love is in a pile of ashes and you only see red flicker embers of the remains of what was.

You’ walked away from someone who you gave so much too and they played with it, they didn’t value it. It was always excuses about being busy.

It was always about them.

You know one day they’ll get there’s coming but for now, you got this pain, that void you are now falling down into and nothing can stop that aching feeling of emptiness.

Nothing they can say will mean anything to you.

Then was the time to do and say it all. They had that chance and they had plenty of time to do so but they didn’t.

They try to reach you but your heart is now closed.

They try to apologise but you only remember all you did and you see their words are nothing but scores they want to keep.

They try again to request and add them but you are afraid now on what else you’re going to hear coming from their mouth or message.

It is so easy to be like some people…who say don’t believe in love, romance, being together and all the things we brought up to believe…to find you believe no more beause you feel love has betrayed you once again.

It changes you.

It changes your personality.

It begins to hide that part of you by wearing a mask…

Have you noticed how it changes how you see everything and even people you meet later on especially for dating and relationships?

Like you use to be open but now you’re closed.

You use to show vulnerability and now you’re scared of being hurt.

Like you use to believe people want honest feelings but you don’t show it anymore because you know most don’t want honest feelings.

Like how you realised most do play games before dating and now you cannot even be direct, real and say how you feel and desire?

You start to act all covert like everyone else.

The memories of disappointments on how you gave chances and how you even changed things that were hard for you with that person, lingers between your chest and it is a memory that burns in your veins everyday,

You can feel it and hear it’s voice when you meet someone.

The pain changes you in ways that that once you had courage to fall deep in love, without hestation, to dive in, to just go for it, yes, go with the flow but now….you don’t.

You’ve changed.

Now you don’t believe much of what you used believe.

You fear to let someone in.

But…

I still do and always will because love for me personally is not defined by someone else but what’s inside of all of us.

So I cannot say to you what makes love in a relationship last.

I am but living day by day, in that moment.

I am appreciating seeing the faces of my lovers.

I am always trying to find ways to make it exciting, adventurous and most of all, to see them smile big whenever we meet.

I am always trying to do things to surprise but because it’s who I am.

I am but trying to enjoy the moment when I see them.

Every kiss is passionate and every love making is intense, rough, passionate and beast like and tender too.

I’m but a human being, fragile like the vase you see on your mantle piece and yet, sharp to cut you from the broken pieces too.

We are all like that in one way and another.

It can bring out the worse in us too.

Many of us walk and love pretending we cannot see our own cracks and many of us embrace them to give us strength for another day to love again.

While some hide back into the shadows of fear of being abandonment - some of us are pioneers of our hearts to keep sailing to the next Island wherever that Island is.

Some of us just keep doing the same repeated patterns to end with the same result over and over again.

We find this to be so, when we think we got all the answers to find something happens, and now these answers slip through our fingers like golden sand, with dreams we once thought possible, are gone.

That’s what love is really about.

That it’s really more about loving yourself because you cannot control the heart of someone else.

At anytime the tide can change.

In that flicker of a moment, who you thought you knew becomes a stranger and now you realise…

The final mystery of love is loving yourself.

You cannot control people and the outcome as much as you think you can. All the words, promises, declaration and even rings and wedding bells, cannot control someone else’s heart.

  • All there is - how long can you…love yourself?
  • How deep and how much you’re going to invest in your self?
  • How big is the fight in you for yourself?
  • How much belief do you have about you and your self worth?
  • How long can you believe in your own courage, in your own beauty, in your own worthiness, in your own gifts, in your own talents, in your own goals, in your ideas and in all that you got to offer?

So much so, that if ever a time came when all comes crumbling down, you will cry, you will feel pain and you will need to take time to heal…

But….

You will always love yourself, whether a person walks in or out of your life. Whether you get fired from a job and whether people don’t accept you or don’t agree with you or even write slurs about you.

I only know that loving yourself from the inside will last until you breathe your final breath. That is all we got.

That is our greatest treasure which so may look for it out there, in some external object or person.

I can never know how long love lasts in relationship with lovers and I don’t want to know. It is that which gives me the courage, the strength, the inspirations, the excitement, the appreciation and the edge over many who do not know how to love themselves.

It makes us rare in a world that sees love as how many people loves them or who loves them, how many like them, how many like their work, how many follow them and how many talk about them in a supporting way - rather than how much we love ourselves.

Yes, it leaves us vulnerable.

But I’ll have it no other way even though it makes me feel vulnerable.
